      <time class="date" data-created-at="2014-05-19T16:04:11.076Z" datetime="2014-05-19T16:04:11.076Z" title="Monday, May 19 2014 4:04 PM"><a href="#comment-3724a840-df6f-11e3-9ede-11160b1c29ca">4 months ago</a></time>
      
    </header>

    <span class="text prose"><p>I have been in this dude&#39;s corner since I read Looking for Alaska on a camp trip several years ago. When someone asks me who my favorite author is, I immediately say him - even if he does write &quot;Young Adult Fiction&quot; and I&#39;m quickly become less of a &#39;young&#39; adult. He&#39;s witty and sarcastic at times, poignant in a non-sappy way, and thought inducing. Many an hour has been spent poring over his books, connecting with people who exist only in his mind. </p>
<p>Being a fan as long as I have been, watching people experience him for the first time is such a rewarding experience. Hearing his name on the radio, seeing him pop up in my e-mail is incredible. I feel like a member of my own family is finally receiving the recognition they&#39;ve been due.</p>
<p>So, go for it John Green. Continue to be awesome and I hope the world never stops loving you for it.</p>
</span>

